&lt;h3 id="configuration"&gt;Configuration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This site uses &lt;strong&gt;KaTeX&lt;/strong&gt; for rendering mathematics. The configured delimiters are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Inline: $...$ or \(...\)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;Display: $$...$$ or \[...\]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Additionally, you can use code blocks for block-level formulas:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;```math
E = mc^2
```
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For &lt;code&gt;vscode&lt;/code&gt;, you might want to ensure your preview settings match these delimiters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good memory is not as bad as a pen.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="permutation"&gt;Permutation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$ A_n^n=n\times(n-1)\times(n-2)\times&amp;hellip;\times2\times1 $&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$ A_n^m=n\times(n-1)\times(n-2)\times&amp;hellip;\times(n-m+1) = \frac{n!}{(n-m)!} $&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="combination"&gt;Combination&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;$ C_n^m=\frac{A_n^m}{A_m^m} = \frac{n!}{m!(n-m)!} $&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>